Here `sink.abort(callback)`: the always-running line `cb = err, err = true` sets `cb = callback` (the original `err`), `err = true`. Then `abort = true`, `read(true, callback)`. Source calls `callback(true)`. So `err` in callback is `true`. This should work on original.

On mutated: if `"function" == typeof err` were the condition, mutated sets `err = false` inside if, then outside if `cb = err` (which is now `false`!), `err = true`. So `cb = false`, `abort = true`, `read(true, false || function(){})` = `read(true, function(){})`. The callback passed to abort is never called!

